# How to Build and Run Otzaria

This document explains how to build and run the Otzaria Torah library application.

## Prerequisites

### For NixOS (Recommended)
- Nix with flakes enabled
- Git

### For Other Linux Distributions
- Rust (rustup)
- Node.js (v20+)
- System dependencies:
  - `sudo apt-get install libgtk-3-0 libblkid1 liblzma5` (Ubuntu/Debian)
  - `sudo dnf install gtk3 webkit2gtk` (Fedora)

### For macOS
- Rust (rustup)
- Node.js (v20+)

### For Windows
- Visual C++ Redistributable
- Rust (rustup)
- Node.js (v20+)

---

## Quick Start (NixOS)

```bash
# 1. Enter the development environment
nix develop

# 2. Install npm dependencies
npm install

# 3. Run the application in development mode
npm run dev
```

---

## Quick Start (Other Systems)

```bash
# 1. Install npm dependencies
npm install

# 2. Run the application in development mode
npm run dev
```

---

## Downloading the Library

The app comes with sample data. To get the full Jewish library:

### Option 1: Download Essential Texts (Quick)

```bash
# This downloads Torah, Mishna, and Pirkei Avot from Sefaria
python3 scripts/download_library.py
```

Select option 1 when prompted.

### Option 2: Download Full Library (Recommended)

```bash
# Make the clone script executable
chmod +x scripts/clone_library.sh

# Run the script
./scripts/clone_library.sh
```

This downloads ~500MB of texts from the otzaria-library repository.

### Option 3: Manual Download

1. Visit: https://github.com/zevisvei/otzaria-library/releases
2. Download the latest release
3. Extract to the `library/` folder

---

## After Downloading the Library

1. Run the app: `npm run dev`
2. The app will automatically index the texts
3. Search for texts like "Genesis", "light", "Moses", etc.

---

## Building for Production

```bash
# Build the application
npm run build

# The built application will be in:
# src-tauri/target/release/bundle/
```

